    <h1>Interac: how it works</h1>
    <p><strong>Interac</strong> is a popular Canadian payment method connected to your bank. Online, you’ll typically see Interac e-Transfer or Interac Online.</p>

    <h2>Basics</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Availability:</strong> Most Canadian banks support Interac e-Transfer.</li>
      <li><strong>Typical limits:</strong> daily/weekly limits depend on your bank tier.</li>
      <li><strong>Fees:</strong> often free or low cost; check your bank’s policy.</li>
      <li><strong>Speed:</strong> transfers are usually near-instant; withdrawals may require verification.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Safety tips</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Enable two-factor authentication in your bank.</li>
      <li>Verify the recipient and reference before sending.</li>
      <li>Use strong, unique passwords for all financial services.</li>
    </ul>

